DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260526
SUMMARY:Deadline: John Hansard Gallery: Open Call for Disabled Artists 2026
  (Future Curators)
DESCRIPTION:Open call from John Hansard Gallery for one disabled artist to 
 collaborate with Occupational Therapy and Engineering students at the Univ
 ersity of Southampton to make or adapt tools that support their artistic p
 ractice. The tools and resulting artwork are displayed in an exhibition at
  John Hansard Gallery in February 2027\, curated by Jess Starns as part of
  the Future Curators Programme\, a disability-justice residency programme 
 for Disabled curators founded by the Disabled artist-led organisation DASH
 . The work involves collaborating with students in July and August\, testi
 ng and refining the tools through autumn\, and creating artwork for the ex
 hibition. ELIGIBILITY: disabled artists living and working within a 40-mil
 e distance of John Hansard Gallery. Submit an Expression of Interest via t
 he gallery's open-call page\; access requirements supported (contact jenni
 fa@jhg.art).\n\nOrganisation: John Hansard Gallery\, with the University o
 f Southampton (part of the DASH Future Curators Programme)\nLocation: With
 in 40 miles of John Hansard Gallery\, Southampton\, UK\nAward: GBP 2\,000 
 artist fee (including up to four meetings with students)\, plus travel exp
 enses\, access costs and a materials budget to be defined. No application 
 fee.\nDuration: Project running July 2026 to a February 2027 exhibition\n\
 nMore: https://jhg.art/events/open-call-disabled-artists/?utm_source=artif
 icialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://jhg.art/events/open-call-disabled-artists/?utm_source=artificia
 lnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Within 40 miles of John Hansard Gallery\, Southampton\, UK
END:VEVENT
