SUMMARY:Deadline: BFI Doc Society: Expanded Screen Fund (UK\, VR/AR/Immersi
 ve Non-Fiction)
DESCRIPTION:The BFI Doc Society Expanded Screen Fund supports ambitious scr
 een-based works of non-fiction intended to reach audiences beyond cinemas\
 , including VR\, AR\, MR\, and 360-degree experiences. Projects must be gr
 ounded in real events\, locations\, or narratives and must demonstrate a c
 lear creative rationale for their technical approach. AMOUNT: £25\,000–
 £150\,000 non-recoupable grant. ELIGIBILITY: producers with a demonstrate
 d track record in delivering immersive work\; UK-based\; projects must mee
 t at least three of six stated priorities: equity/diversity/inclusion\, au
 dience impact\, talent development\, creative risk-taking\, UK-wide access
 \, and environmental sustainability. DEADLINE: 22 June 2026 at 1pm UK time
 . APPLY via the BFI Doc Society website. Contact: hellobfi@docsociety.org.
 \n\nOrganisation: BFI Doc Society\nLocation: UK (projects must demonstrate
  UK-wide benefit)\nAward: £25\,000–£150\,000 non-recoupable grant. No 
 application fee.\nDuration: Project-based\; feature-length or series immer
 sive non-fiction works\n\nMore: https://bfi.docsociety.org/funds/expanded-
 screen?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://bfi.docsociety.org/funds/expanded-screen?utm_source=artificialn
 ouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:UK (projects must demonstrate UK-wide benefit)
END:VEVENT
