SUMMARY:Deadline: BFI Doc Society: Made of Truth – Short Non-Fiction Film
  Fund (UK)
DESCRIPTION:BFI Doc Society's Made of Truth fund supports early-career UK f
 ilmmakers making non-fiction live-action or animated short films of 5–40
  minutes. Up to 13 projects are funded per annual round. AMOUNT: up to £2
 5\,000 per project. ELIGIBILITY: early-career directors and producers who 
 are UK residents\; teams must have at least two people (a producer and a d
 irector)\; directors cannot have received a commercial distribution deal f
 or a non-fiction feature in the last five years\; a reasonable proportion 
 of early-career crew is required. Applications must meet at least three of
  six priorities: equity/diversity/inclusion\, audience impact\, talent dev
 elopment\, creative risk\, UK-wide access\, and environmental sustainabili
 ty. OPENS: 18 May 2026 at 1pm UK time. DEADLINE: 1 July 2026 at 1pm UK tim
 e. APPLY via the BFI Doc Society website. Contact: hellobfi@docsociety.org
 .\n\nOrganisation: BFI Doc Society\nLocation: UK (both director and produc
 er must be UK residents)\nAward: Up to £25\,000 non-recoupable grant. No 
 application fee.\nDuration: Short films 5–40 minutes\; up to 13 projects
  funded per year\n\nMore: https://bfi.docsociety.org/funds/made-of-truth?u
 tm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://bfi.docsociety.org/funds/made-of-truth?utm_source=artificialnou
 veaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:UK (both director and producer must be UK residents)
END:VEVENT
