SUMMARY:Deadline: CRASSH 25th Anniversary Exhibition: Knowledge in a Fractu
 red World
DESCRIPTION:The Centre for Research in the Arts\, Social Sciences and Human
 ities (CRASSH) at the University of Cambridge marks its 25th anniversary w
 ith an open-call exhibition on the theme Knowledge in a Fractured World: h
 ow knowledge is produced\, contested\, and shared in a fragmented age. Acc
 epts 2D\, 3D\, video\, film\, and sound work\; a strong thematic fit for c
 ritical data and research-based practices. Open worldwide\, free to enter\
 , no commission on sales. Deadline 31 July 2026.\n\nOrganisation: CRASSH\,
  University of Cambridge\nLocation: Cambridge\, United Kingdom (Alison Ric
 hard Building). Open worldwide.\nAward: Exhibition from 5 October to 11 De
 cember 2026\; no commission taken on sales. Free to enter.\nDuration: Exhi
 bition 5 October to 11 December 2026.\n\nMore: https://arbart.crassh.cam.a
 c.uk/call-for-art-knowledge-in-a-fractured-world/?utm_source=artificialnou
 veaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://arbart.crassh.cam.ac.uk/call-for-art-knowledge-in-a-fractured-w
 orld/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Cambridge\, United Kingdom (Alison Richard Building). Open worldwi
 de.
END:VEVENT
